cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.GT

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on the performance analysis and optimization of a cellular network consisting of unmanned aerial vehicle (UAV) base stations (BSs) and ground BSs, which involves networking and internet architecture aspects. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses the multi-cell coverage probability and the volume spectral efficiency of the network, which are related to information theory. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes a control-data plane-split architecture for the network, which involves systems and control aspects. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper discusses the payload data transmission in the network, which is related to multimedia. 
5. cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) - The paper uses stochastic geometry to propose a 3D location distribution model of the UAVs, which is related to game theory.
